# Ikigai Map — Example
# This is an example file. Copy to memory/ikigai.md and fill in your details.
# CONSTITUTION §8: The live file is gitignored. Only this .example is committed.
# Populated by ikigai-compass.md and 15_ikigai-audit.md.

---

## Last Reviewed

last_reviewed: "YYYY-MM-DD"
next_audit: "YYYY-MM-DD"
# Recommended: every 6 months, or at every biannual DRPC review

---

## Four-Quadrant Map

passion: ""
# What areas of CS/technology genuinely absorb you? When do you lose track of time?
# Example: "Building things that work in the real world — especially hardware + software systems"

strength: ""
# What are you unusually good at — technically or otherwise?
# Example: "Understanding complex systems quickly; translating research into understandable explanations"

world_need: ""
# If your research succeeds, who benefits and how?
# Example: "Farmers in Karnataka who lose crops to unpredicted weather events"

vocation: ""
# What kind of career do you want, and what would you want to be paid to do?
# Example: "Applied AI researcher at a company that deploys systems in the real world"

---

## Overlap Zones

passion_x_strength: ""
# What emerges at the intersection of passion and strength?
# Example: "Building ML systems that actually work in deployment — not just in notebooks"

passion_x_world_need: ""
# Example: "Using AI to solve problems that affect real communities, especially in India"

strength_x_vocation: ""
# Example: "Being a trusted technical lead or researcher who ships working products"

world_need_x_vocation: ""
# Example: "Solving India-specific problems that are underserved by global research agendas"

ikigai_centre: ""
# The intersection of all four, in one sentence (if it has emerged)
# Example: "Building AI systems for Indian agriculture that actually get deployed and used"
# Leave blank if not yet defined — it takes time

---

## Alignment Assessment

alignment_status: "Green"
# Options: Green (strong) | Amber — [specific gap] | Red — [significant misalignment]

alignment_rationale: ""
# Why is the current alignment green/amber/red?

tension_areas: []
# Any specific areas where research and values are pulling in different directions
# Example: ["Research domain is technically narrow but career goal is broad AI leadership"]

---

## Renewal Actions

renewal_actions: []
# Specific actions to address alignment gaps
# Example:
# - "Add a real-world deployment case study to the thesis to strengthen vocation alignment"
# - "Visit one farming community to ground the world-need in observable reality"
# - "Talk to 3 industry practitioners about the career pathway to AI team lead"

---

## History

audit_history:
  - date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
    status: "Green / Amber / Red"
    key_insight: ""
    actions_taken: []
